article.headline: Siena 76, Loyola, Md. 56
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Clarence Jackson scored 24 points and Edwin Ubiles added 22 to lead Siena to an easy 76-56 win over Loyola of Maryland on Monday night. Jackson also finished with seven steals for the Saints (11-4, 4-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won five games in a row. Ronald Moore dished out 11 assists and had four steals with five turnovers. Siena pulled away early from the Greyhounds (8-6, 1-3), taking a 33-17 lead late in the first half after Jackson's steal and three-point play. He went 8-for-18 from the floor and 6-for-8 from the free throw line. Loyola, which shot 55.2 percent in the second half, still was unable to pull closer than 11 points as the Saints pushed their margin to 30 on Kyle Downey's three-point play with 7:09 to play. Jamal Barney was the only Loyola player to score in double figures with 15 points and six assists.
